706707f-a.title: Brooklyn: Sheepshead Bay Road - 14th Street (East)
706707f-a.text:
Sheepshead Bay Road, south side, from and including East 14th Street,
to, but not including Av3., ''y''. All the houses seen are frame; the
house on the corner has a brick font. (Sheepshead Bay Road, is arbit-
rarily set to run cast and west from East 13th Street, to Jerome Ave).
July 9, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

706708f-a.title: Brooklyn: Sheepshead Bay Road - 14th Street (East)
706708f-a.text:
(1)
Sheepshead Bay Road, at the S.E. corner of East 14th Street, show-
ing the St. Mark's R.C. Church, which was organised in 1868. This edi-
fice was demolished by fire on February 24, 1929.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPR ODUCED.
(2)
The same, showimg a later view
October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE RER ODUCED.

702546f-a.title: Brooklyn: 14th Street (East) - Sheepshead Bay Road
702546f-a.text:
East 14th Street, west side, from but not including Sheepshead Bay
Road, to, but not including Voorhies Ave. All the houses are frame.
(Sheepshead Bay Poad, is arbitrarily set to run east and west from
East 13th Street to Jerome Ave).
